      "message": "[Critical] Line 2148: The race protection relies on millisecond-resolution timestamps always changing, but two local removals can occur within the same millisecond. In that case handlePendingConversation() can treat an in-flight re-invite as still valid and clear a newer tombstone, resurrecting a conversation the user removed again. Use a monotonic per-conversation removal generation/token, or otherwise compare against state that is guaranteed to change on every removal rather than nowMs().\n```suggestion\n// Store and compare a removal generation/counter updated on every local removal,\n// not only the millisecond timestamp.\nstd::optional\u003cuint64_t\u003e removedGeneration;\n```",
